____________________________________________________________________________

Use this array class for arrays of string or binary properties of
any size.  StringArrays, HugeStringArrays and BinaryArrays all have
a limit to the size of each element, whereas, using this array
class, the string and binary properties are defined with a length
of maximum.

The array elements are instances of the CnEcArrayObject class, which
has the following two properties:

	binaryValue   Type = Binary, protected length = Maximum
	StringValue   Type = String, protected length = Maximum

Because these properties are protected, the developer must use the
get/set methods on the CnEcArayObject class to reference them.

Refer to the BaseSchema Developer Guide for details of the array's
methods and examples of its use.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="jssxs_array"/>
    <JadeMethod name="addBinary" id="c442590e-2db5-4dea-96ac-b1e638b7e42d">
        <lockReceiver/>
        <updating/>
        <source>addBinary(pBinaryValue:Binary):Integer updating;
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Created:		29 August 1999 by cnwdad1
//
// Purpose:		Adds a new element to the array with the specified binary value.
//
// Parameters:	pBinaryValue (Binary) - The binary value for the new array element.
// Returns:		Integer - The index of the new array element.
//
// Changed On	Changed By	Reason
// ----------	----------	-------------------------------------------------------
//
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
vars
	arrayElement	: JSSArrayElement;
	index			: Integer;

begin
	arrayElement	:=	self.createEntry();
	arrayElement.setBinaryValue(pBinaryValue);
	index			:=	self.size() + 1;
	self.atPut(index, arrayElement);
epilog
	return index;
end;</source>
        <Parameter name="pBinaryValue" type="Binary"/>
        <ReturnType type="Integer"/>
    </JadeMethod>
    <JadeMethod name="addBinaryAt" id="4b5b2c14-0957-4095-9160-7c784da92e22">
        <lockReceiver/>
        <updating/>
        <source>addBinaryAt(pIndex:Integer; pBinaryValue:Binary) updating;
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Created:		29 August 1999 by cnwdad1
//
// Purpose:		Inserts a new element into the array at the specified index position
//				and with the specified binary value.
//
// Parameters:	pBinaryValue (Binary) - The binary value for the new array element.
// Returns:		Nothing
//
// Changed On	Changed By	Reason
// ----------	----------	-------------------------------------------------------
//
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
vars
	arrayElement	: JSSArrayElement;

begin
	arrayElement	:=	self.createEntry();
	arrayElement.setBinaryValue(pBinaryValue);
	self.atPut(pIndex, arrayElement);
end;</source>
        <Parameter name="pIndex" type="Integer"/>
        <Parameter name="pBinaryValue" type="Binary"/>
    </JadeMethod>
